WEBVTT

00:07.865 --> 00:11.217
Boys, hurry up; you're
gonna be late for the bus!

00:11.219 --> 00:13.186
Babe, we're pretty much on fumes
till the end of the month.

00:13.188 --> 00:14.988
Which one of these bills
you want me to pay first?

00:14.990 --> 00:17.807
Well, the gas company's not
gonna ding us for 15 days.

00:17.809 --> 00:18.941
Pay the power bill.

00:18.943 --> 00:20.410
You're a genius.

00:20.412 --> 00:21.611
Remember,
tonight's the night

00:21.613 --> 00:23.479
that me and the boys
are gonna be home late.

00:23.481 --> 00:26.115
Right, the birthday party
or something.

00:26.117 --> 00:27.650
Oh, Scotty Trevino.

00:27.652 --> 00:30.152
Him and 20 of his closest
buddies I got.

00:30.154 --> 00:31.187
An arcade,

00:31.189 --> 00:33.206
then burgers
and a movie.

00:33.208 --> 00:34.257
Good luck.

00:34.259 --> 00:35.591
Thank you.

00:35.593 --> 00:37.493
And you remember what you're
doing after work, right?

00:37.495 --> 00:39.262
Yeah, coming home, drink a beer

00:39.264 --> 00:40.296
and watch TV.

00:40.298 --> 00:42.632
Uh, no, you got to go to, uh,

00:42.634 --> 00:44.166
here.

00:44.168 --> 00:45.518
Wojcik...

00:45.520 --> 00:47.353
Wojcik Polish Bakery.

00:47.355 --> 00:49.305
Yeah, we used to go there
as kids when my old man

00:49.307 --> 00:50.556
did a stint in the 5-4.
Well, apparently,

00:50.558 --> 00:52.608
their chocolate
cheesecake is amazing.

00:52.610 --> 00:54.677
Okay.
I want to have it for family dinner.

00:54.679 --> 00:56.362
Okay, but family dinner's
not till Sunday, babe.

00:56.364 --> 00:58.364
Why do I have to go get
the cheesecake tonight?

00:58.366 --> 00:59.615
Because they're not
open on Sunday

00:59.617 --> 01:01.350
and they don't take orders
over the phone.

01:01.352 --> 01:02.618
Fine, yeah, all right.

01:02.620 --> 01:05.038
I will go tonight
and then I'm gonna come home,

01:05.040 --> 01:08.023
have a beer, watch TV
in my underwear.

01:08.025 --> 01:09.826
I'll wait for you.

01:12.379 --> 01:14.497
<i>Reagan,</i>

01:14.499 --> 01:15.498
Lansing!

01:15.500 --> 01:17.550
Where are we on
that bodega shooting?

01:17.552 --> 01:18.634
We're nowhere, Sarge.

01:18.636 --> 01:20.035
Couple kids saw
the shooter, but it's

01:20.037 --> 01:22.371
12th Street Boyz territory,
so nobody's talking.

01:22.373 --> 01:24.039
Uh-huh, how about
your hit and run?

01:24.041 --> 01:25.207
That one's even colder.

01:25.209 --> 01:26.642
You know we're
in the business

01:26.644 --> 01:28.010
of closing cases, right?

01:28.012 --> 01:30.379
Come on, you can't be
busting our balls, Sarge.

01:30.381 --> 01:32.598
Well, Chief of D's
just did a number on mine,

01:32.600 --> 01:33.900
so I'm spreading the wealth.

01:33.902 --> 01:35.551
Then you spoke
too soon.

01:35.553 --> 01:37.186
That string of random assaults
in Greenpoint?

01:37.188 --> 01:38.988
We just sweet-talked
victim number four

01:38.990 --> 01:41.107
into explaining
how they're not so random.

01:41.109 --> 01:42.224
Uh-huh, which is?

01:42.226 --> 01:43.693
They're all clients
of a local bookie

01:43.695 --> 01:46.829
named Alan Greer-- the wounds
are sort of a warning to pay up.

01:46.831 --> 01:48.698
So your vic can I.D.
the attacker as Greer?

01:48.700 --> 01:49.665
Well, no,

01:49.667 --> 01:51.167
but apparently he keeps
a very detailed

01:51.169 --> 01:53.336
little black book, so we get
our hands on that book...

01:53.338 --> 01:54.737
You connect him
to all the victims

01:54.739 --> 01:56.672
and get them
to presses charges, too.

01:56.674 --> 01:58.758
Wow, you know,
I bet you can't

01:58.760 --> 02:00.009
wait till tomorrow, Sarge.

02:00.011 --> 02:00.960
Why's that?

02:00.962 --> 02:02.578
Because you get
smarter every day.

02:02.580 --> 02:03.880
Yeah.

02:03.882 --> 02:06.299
I'll head over to the A.D.A.'s
and try to get

02:06.301 --> 02:08.300
a search warrant
for Greer's place.

02:10.554 --> 02:12.254
What do you mean "no"?

02:12.256 --> 02:13.556
As in "not yes""

02:13.558 --> 02:15.274
Come on, Saul,
this bookie's going around

02:15.276 --> 02:17.894
handing out beat-downs
like it's candy on Halloween.

02:17.896 --> 02:20.095
On the word of a gambling
addict with a head injury.

02:20.097 --> 02:22.482
Yeah, who also says that
this bookie, this guy Greer,

02:22.484 --> 02:23.866
he keeps everything
written down

02:23.868 --> 02:25.651
on a little black book
in his safe.

02:25.653 --> 02:26.869
Come on, we get this book,

02:26.871 --> 02:29.655
we can close five
assault cases at one time.

02:29.657 --> 02:31.207
All right.

02:31.209 --> 02:33.292
But I'm swamped; won't be
till the middle of next week.

02:33.294 --> 02:34.777
Saul, you're a former
cop yourself.

02:34.779 --> 02:36.629
You know I got to
move on this now.

02:36.631 --> 02:37.947
Fine!

02:37.949 --> 02:39.799
Monday. Best I can do.

02:39.801 --> 02:41.584
All right, thank you.

02:41.586 --> 02:43.970
Are you seeing another
A.D.A. behind my back?

02:43.972 --> 02:45.805
Well, you know, I can't have
everybody thinking

02:45.807 --> 02:47.924
I run to my sister
every time I need something.

02:47.926 --> 02:49.926
Right? They might start
thinking you're smart.

02:49.928 --> 02:51.427
Did you go to
the bakery yet?

02:51.429 --> 02:52.762
How do you know
about that?

02:52.764 --> 02:54.981
Linda asked me to mention it
if you happened to stop by,

02:54.983 --> 02:57.800
but, look, get me some of those
<i>paczkis;</i> I love those things.

02:57.802 --> 03:00.019
Fine, fine, I'm going
after work, okay?

03:00.021 --> 03:02.155
I know, and then
I hear you have a date

03:02.157 --> 03:04.073
with your couch
in your underwear.

03:04.075 --> 03:06.809
Does she have
to tell you everything?

03:06.811 --> 03:08.528
That's what I said.

03:10.814 --> 03:14.167
♪

